New born EchoWaves

generated with a command:
 rails echowaves --edge --skip-activerecord --skip-testunit --skip-prototype

Intended infrastructure:
	ruby 1.9
	--edge (rails 3)
	--skip-activerecord (will use MongoMapper)
	--skip-testunit (will use RSpec 2 with Cucumber)
	--skip-prototype (will use JQuery 1.4)
  web sockets (will use an alternative solution for non supported browsers)

Development environment setup
  # Install RVM
  mkdir -p ~/.rvm/src/ && cd ~/.rvm/src && rm -rf ./rvm/ && git clone git://github.com/wayneeseguin/rvm.git && cd rvm && ./install

  # install ruby 1.9
  rvm install 1.9.1

  # you might need to specify the readline folder rvm install 1.8.7 -C --enable-shared,--with-readline-dir=/usr/local

  # user the installed ruby 1.9 with a dedicated gemset
  rvm 1.9.1%rails3

  gem install tzinfo builder i18n memcache-client rack \
    rake rack-test rack-mount erubis mail text-format \
    thor bundler

  gem install rails --prerelease


  # check to see if you have rails 3.0.0 beta
  rails --version

Installation of ruby gems
  # we are using some pre-released gems which works with Rails 3
  and last, do "bundle install" to install all the dependencies


Know issues
  there is an issue with the mongoid initializer loading the database.mongo.yml file
  at this moment you should configure your databases in config/initializers/mongoid instead

  cucumber don't work

